---
import SharedPageLayout from "../components/SharedPageLayout.astro";
---

<SharedPageLayout title="Straight Answers | Done Deal Digital FAQ" bodyClass="bg-concrete font-dmsans text-navy">
    <Fragment slot="head">
<meta charset="utf-8"/>
<meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" name="viewport"/>

<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com?plugins=forms,container-queries"></script>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Bebas+Neue&amp;family=DM+Sans:wght@400;500;700&amp;family=Work+Sans:wght@400;700&amp;family=Material+Symbols+Outlined:wght,FILL@100..700,0..1&amp;display=swap" rel="stylesheet"/>
<script id="tailwind-config">
        tailwind.config = {
            darkMode: "class",
            theme: {
                extend: {
                    colors: {
                        "primary": "#FF7B00", // Construction Orange
                        "navy": "#0B1D33",
                        "concrete": "#E2E8F0",
                        "background-light": "#f6f6f8",
                        "background-dark": "#0B1D33",
                        "grid-gray": "rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05)"
                    },
                    fontFamily: {
                        "display": ["Work Sans", "sans-serif"],
                        "bebas": ["Bebas Neue", "cursive"],
                        "dmsans": ["DM Sans", "sans-serif"]
                    },
                    borderRadius: {
                        "none": "0",
                        "DEFAULT": "0",
                        "lg": "0",
                        "xl": "0",
                        "full": "9999px"
                    },
                    borderWidth: {
                        "3": "3px"
                    }
                },
            },
        }
    </script>
<style type="text/tailwindcss">
        @tailwind base;
        @tailwind components;
        @tailwind utilities;

        @layer utilities {
            .graph-paper {
                background-size: 40px 40px;
                background-image: 
                    linear-gradient(to right, rgba(255,255,255,0.05) 1px, transparent 1px),
                    linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(255,255,255,0.05) 1px, transparent 1px);
            }
            .block-shadow {
                box-shadow: 6px 6px 0px 0px rgba(11, 29, 51, 1);
            }
            .block-shadow-orange {
                box-shadow: 6px 6px 0px 0px #FF7B00;
            }
            .diagonal-stripes {
                background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, rgba(11, 29, 51, 0.05) 0, rgba(11, 29, 51, 0.05) 10px, transparent 10px, transparent 20px);
            }
        }
        .bebas-heavy {
            font-weight: 700;
            letter-spacing: 0.02em;
        }
        details > summary::-webkit-details-marker {
            display: none;
        }
        details[open] summary .plus-icon {
            transform: rotate(45deg);
        }
    </style>
</Fragment>

<section class="relative bg-navy overflow-hidden border-b-2 border-navy">
<div class="absolute inset-0 graph-paper opacity-40"></div>
<div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-20 py-24 relative z-10">
<div class="max-w-3xl">
<div class="inline-block border-2 border-primary px-4 py-1 mb-6">
<span class="text-white font-bebas bebas-heavy text-xl tracking-[.2em]">FAQ</span>
</div>
<h1 class="font-bebas bebas-heavy text-7xl md:text-8xl text-white leading-[0.85] uppercase mb-8">
                STRAIGHT ANSWERS FOR <span class="text-primary">BUSY OWNERS.</span>
            </h1>
<p class="text-concrete text-xl md:text-2xl leading-relaxed font-medium">
                If you don’t see your question here, reach out. We’ll give you a straight answer.
            </p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<main class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 relative">
<div class="absolute inset-0 diagonal-stripes opacity-30 pointer-events-none"></div>
<div class="relative z-10 space-y-20">
<section>
<h2 class="font-bebas bebas-heavy text-5xl text-navy mb-8 flex items-center gap-4">
                GETTING STARTED
                <span class="h-1 flex-grow bg-navy/10"></span>
</h2>
<div class="space-y-4">
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">How does the process work?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            We begin with a fit call, then request a brief set of access items. After that we map scope, set timeline, and launch once assets are in.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">How long does it take to build a website?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
 </summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            Most custom sites are built and launched in 2 to 3 weeks once assets and feedback are available.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">Do I need to provide photos or written content?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            Some photos and basic service details help. If you don’t have everything ready, we help you prioritize what matters first.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">Can you work with my current website, domain, or Google Business Profile?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            Yes. We work with existing domains, current sites, and Google Business Profiles when migration or setup makes sense.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
</div>
</section>

<section>
<h2 class="font-bebas bebas-heavy text-5xl text-navy mb-8 flex items-center gap-4">
                PRICING &amp; SCOPE
                <span class="h-1 flex-grow bg-navy/10"></span>
</h2>
<div class="space-y-4">
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">How much does a website cost?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            Price depends on scope and complexity. We share a fixed proposal after the fit call and define exactly what is included.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">What’s included, and what counts as extra?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            We include the essentials needed for a usable marketing site. Extra work is listed up front, such as ongoing ad management or advanced content production.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">Are there ongoing costs after launch?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            Hosting, ads, and optional maintenance are typically separate from initial build pricing and are documented before launch.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">Do I own my website and accounts?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            Yes. Access and ownership are yours. We set this clearly in the project agreement and handoff list.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
</div>
</section>

<section>
<h2 class="font-bebas bebas-heavy text-5xl text-navy mb-8 flex items-center gap-4">
                WORKING WITH US
                <span class="h-1 flex-grow bg-navy/10"></span>
</h2>
<div class="space-y-4">
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">How many revisions are included?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            Our standard scope includes one structured revision round after launch, focused on agreed goals.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">Will I be able to update the site myself?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            Yes. We use straightforward editing workflows and train your team on the parts you need to own.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">Do you lock me into a contract?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            We use agreements aligned to scope and duration. We don’t build fake lock-in structures, and recurring work is optional.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
</div>
</section>

<section>
<h2 class="font-bebas bebas-heavy text-5xl text-navy mb-8 flex items-center gap-4">
                SEO &amp; ADS
                <span class="h-1 flex-grow bg-navy/10"></span>
</h2>
<div class="space-y-4">
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">How long does local SEO take?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            It is compounding work. Most clients see clearer signals over 60–120 days with consistent follow-through.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">What ad budget do I need?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            Budget depends on service area and call value. We recommend enough spend to collect meaningful lead quality signals in the first cycle.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">Do you run Google Ads, LSAs, and Facebook ads?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            We focus on Google Search ads and Local Services Ads where fit is strong. We won’t use channels that don’t fit your process.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">Do you guarantee rankings or leads?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            No. We guarantee process, transparency, and a structured reporting rhythm. Outcome depends on market conditions and execution.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
</div>
</section>

<section>
<h2 class="font-bebas bebas-heavy text-5xl text-navy mb-8 flex items-center gap-4">
                TECHNICAL
                <span class="h-1 flex-grow bg-navy/10"></span>
</h2>
<div class="space-y-4">
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">Do you help with Google Business Profile?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            Yes. We support GBP setup and ongoing hygiene when it affects local discovery.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">How do you handle hosting?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            Hosting and deployment are part of the technical setup. We keep it simple, secure, and easy to hand off.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-navy block-shadow">
<summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
<span class="font-bold text-xl uppercase tracking-tight">Will my site work on mobile?</span>
<span class="plus-icon material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl transition-transform duration-200">add_box</span>
</summary>
<div class="px-6 pb-6 pt-2 border-t border-navy/10">
<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                            Yes. Mobile usability is built into every deliverable, with clear call-to-actions and lightweight pages.
                        </p>
</div>
</details>
</div>
</section>
</div>
</main>

<section class="py-24 bg-concrete">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<div class="bg-white border-4 border-navy p-12 relative block-shadow-orange text-center">
<h2 class="font-bebas bebas-heavy text-7xl text-navy mb-6">STILL HAVE QUESTIONS? <span class="text-primary">LET'S TALK.</span></h2>
<p class="text-2xl text-slate-600 mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">If you don’t see your question here, reach out and we’ll handle it directly.</p>
<div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-8">
<a href="/contact" class="bg-primary hover:bg-orange-600 text-white px-12 py-6 font-bold text-2xl uppercase tracking-widest border-2 border-navy block-shadow w-full md:w-auto inline-block text-center transition-transform hover:-translate-y-1">
                    CONTACT US
                </a>
<div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-navy font-bold text-xl">
<span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-3xl">phone_in_talk</span>
<span>CALL US: (555) 123-4567</span>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

</SharedPageLayout>
